# NS0921 Export Error: Invalid Subsidiary Reference

If you see the error message **“NS0921 Export Error: Invalid subsidiary reference [X]. Please ensure the report, user, accounts, tags, and categories all use the subsidiary selected in the workspace.”**, it means there is a subsidiary mismatch.

NetSuite requires all elements tied to the export to belong to the same subsidiary.

---

## Why the NS0921 Export Error Happens

The NS0921 export error occurs when one or more of the following items are associated with a different subsidiary than the one selected in the Workspace:

- The report creator or submitter (employee record)
- The expense category
- Tags (Department, Class, Location, Project, Customer)
- The export account
- The default payable account
- The vendor record

If any of these are tied to a different subsidiary, NetSuite rejects the export.

---

## How to Fix the NS0921 Export Error

### Step 1: Confirm the Workspace Subsidiary

In Expensify:

1. Go to the **navigation tabs on the left** and select **Workspaces**.
2. Select your Workspace.
3. Select **Accounting**.
4. Confirm the subsidiary selected for the NetSuite connection.

---

### Step 2: Verify Subsidiary Alignment in NetSuite

In NetSuite, confirm that all of the following are:

- Active  
- Assigned to the same subsidiary as the Workspace  

Check:

- The employee record for the report creator or submitter  
- The vendor record (if applicable)  
- The expense category used on the report  
- Any tags applied (Department, Class, Location, Project, Customer)  
- The export account or payable account  

If any item is assigned to a different subsidiary, update it so it matches the connected subsidiary.

---

### Step 3: Sync the Connection in Expensify

After confirming all records are aligned:

On web:

1. Go to **Workspaces > [Workspace Name] > Accounting**.
2. Click the **three-dot icon** next to the NetSuite connection.
3. Click **Sync now**.

On mobile:

1. Tap **Workspaces > [Workspace Name] > Accounting**.
2. Tap the **three-dot icon** next to the NetSuite connection.
3. Tap **Sync now**.

Retry exporting the report once the sync completes.

---

# FAQ

## Does the NS0921 Export Error affect only one report?

It affects any report that includes records tied to a different subsidiary than the one selected in the Workspace.

## Do I need NetSuite admin access to fix the NS0921 Export Error?

Yes. Updating subsidiary assignments for employees, vendors, categories, or accounts requires appropriate NetSuite permissions.
